vectorData.altText: 2. This image demonstrates an example of a(n) ______________ hydrocephalus.
That’s right!  The image demonstrates an example of an obstructive hydrocephalus. Notice the enlargement of the lateral and third ventricles but not the fourth.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

Hydrocephalus is characterized by:
an increase in CSF volume
enlargement of one or more ventricles
an increase in intracranial pressure
Hydrocephalus occurs with either:
blockage of CSF mvt; this is obstructive hydrocephalus.
CSF production continues regardless of a blockage of CSF flow. Blockage occurs most commonly at narrowings of the ventricular system, such as the cerebral aqueduct or one or both interventricular foramina. 
The location of the blockage is indicated by pattern of ventricular enlargement; the ventricles upstream of the blockage are enlarged, those downstream are not.
impaired absorption of CSF; this is communicating hydrocephalus.
This can occur with agenesis of the arachnoid granulations, blockage of the arachnoid villi, or blockage within subarachnoid space, for instance following a subarachnoid hemorrhage.
All ventricles are enlarged in communicating hydrocephalus.
